{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"source": "pdfs/Population-synthesis-using-incomplete-microsample.pdf", "page_numbers": "[4]", "headings": "['3.1.1. Population Data']"}, "page_content": "3.1.1. Population Data\nWe require ground-truth population data without missing information to test the suggested methodology's ability to train WGAN-GP models with missing information. Utilizing the survey, we generate a complete population dataset by reproducing each row's weight value. We removed all rows with missing data from the whole population dataset and kept 17 individual and household features. Table 1 lists the travel survey dataset attributes used in the research, including 13 for individuals and 4 for households. We designate this dataset as h-population , which serves as the reference dataset or 'ground truth' for subsequent analysis.", "type": "Document"}}